#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:2
msgid "add-mtls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:4
msgid ""
"In your current configuration, microservices communicate using HTTP, "
"which means the traffic is not encrypted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:7
msgid ""
"Istio helps solve this problem by encrypting the traffic between the "
"sidecars. This leaves only the traffic inside the application pods, and "
"traffic between microservices and sidecars unencrypted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:11
msgid ""
"In this module, you enable Istio `mutual TLS authentication "
"</docs/reference/glossary#mutual-tls-authentication>`_ for the traffic "
"between microservices in your namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:15
msgid ""
"First, check that your microservices accept unencrypted traffic. Send an "
"HTTP request to ``ratings`` from your testing pod, ``sleep``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:21
msgid ""
"-o jsonpath=‘{.items[0].metadata.name}’) – curl "
"http://ratings:9080/ratings/7 "
"{“id”:7,“ratings”:{“Reviewer1”:5,“Reviewer2”:4}}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:25
msgid "Enable mutual TLS authentication in your namespace:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:30
msgid ""
"authentication.istio.io/v1alpha1 kind: Policy metadata: name: default "
"spec: peers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:33
msgid ""
"mtls: {} EOF $ kubectl apply -f {{< github_file "
">}}/samples/bookinfo/networking/destination-rule-all-mtls.yaml"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:38
msgid ""
"In case you did not enable the Istio Ingress Gateway, run the following "
"command, in addition to the command above. {{< /warning >}}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:45
msgid ""
"authentication.istio.io/v1alpha1 kind: Policy metadata: name: disable-"
"mtls-productpage spec: targets:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:48
msgid ""
"name: productpage peers: [] — apiVersion: networking.istio.io/v1alpha3 "
"kind: DestinationRule metadata: name: productpage spec: host: productpage"
" trafficPolicy: tls: mode: DISABLE EOF"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:53
msgid ""
"Access your application’s web page to verify that everything continues to"
" work as expected. Recall that you recently changed the URL of the "
"application, e.g. \\ ``http://istio.tutorial.bookinfo.com/productpage``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:58
msgid ""
"Verify that your microservices do not accept unencrypted traffic anymore."
" Send an HTTP request to ``ratings`` from your testing pod, ``sleep``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:65
msgid ""
"-o jsonpath=‘{.items[0].metadata.name}’) – curl "
"http://ratings:9080/ratings/7 curl: (56) Recv failure: Connection reset "
"by peer command terminated with exit code 56"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:69
msgid ""
"The last command failed as expected because your testing pod has no Istio"
" sidecar and it sent an unencrypted HTTP request to your service that "
"requires mutual TLS Authentication. Now communication is limited between "
"services where Istio sidecars are injected and only if the traffic is "
"encrypted by the sidecar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:75
msgid ""
"Access the Istio dashboard at http://my-istio-dashboard.io/dashboard/db"
"/istio-mesh-dashboard. Check ``ratings`` in *Istio Service Dashboard*. "
"Notice that now a lock icon with text ``mTLS`` appears in *Service "
"Workload*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:85
msgid ""
"Check your Kiali console, http://my-kiali.io/kiali/console, the graph of "
"your namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:88
msgid ""
"In the *Display* drop-down menu mark the *Security* check box to see "
"locks that designate mutual TLS on the graph’s edges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:93
msgid "You might zoom in to the graph view to see the lock icons clearly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/add-mtls/index.rst:101
msgid ""
"Note that you made all the traffic between the pods in your cluster "
"encrypted, transparently to your microservice, while changing neither "
"code nor configuration of your microservices."
msgstr ""

